		<category><![CDATA[Globe]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=817</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/globe-offers-free-facebook-access"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-27-09-26-24-168x300.png" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="Screenshot_2013-10-27-09-26-24" title="" /></a>Globe Telecom recently launched yet another free service to millions of its subscribers nationwide &#8211; free unlimited access to Facebook mobile. 36 million Globe and TM postpaid and prepaid subscribers get to enjoy accessing their Facebook accounts anytime of the day, free of charge without even the need of a wifi connection or a data plan. The service includes access to Facebook through native application and the mobile site m.facecook.com. Announced  Monday night, October 21st, the service will be enjoyed until[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-27-09-26-24.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-818" alt="Screenshot_2013-10-27-09-26-24" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-27-09-26-24-168x300.png" width="168" height="300" /></a></p>
<p>Globe Telecom recently launched yet another free service to millions of its subscribers nationwide &#8211; free unlimited access to Facebook mobile. 36 million Globe and TM postpaid and prepaid subscribers get to enjoy accessing their Facebook accounts anytime of the day, free of charge without even the need of a wifi connection or a data plan. The service includes access to Facebook through native application and the mobile site <a href="http://m.facecook.com/" target="_blank">m.facecook.com</a>. Announced  Monday night, October 21st, the service will be enjoyed until January next year.</p>
<p>This service is made possible through the partnership between Globe and Facebook. In a statement Ernest Cu, president and CEO of Globe said &#8220;Globe has solved all these issues because for an initial three months, Facebook will be free to users of Globe in the Philippines&#8221; referring to hindrances that keeps Facebook users accessing their account through their mobile devices &#8211; not enough prepaid credits for instance.</p>
<p>During the launch, Chris Daniels (Vice President of Partnership at Facebook) said there is a good opportunity to connect to more people in the Philippines with about a hundred million people and about 30 million with Facebook accounts. &#8220;Philippines to us creates an enormous opportunity to connect to more people. There are a hundred million people in the Philippines and only about 30 million of them access the internet every month, so we need to connect to more people there&#8221; said Daniels.</p>
<fb:like href=http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/globe-offers-free-facebook-access font=></fb:like>]]></content:encoded>
