		<title>Android 4.3 update for Samsung Galaxy S4</title>
		<link>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/android-4-3-update-for-samsung-galaxy-s4</link>
		<comments>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/android-4-3-update-for-samsung-galaxy-s4#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Sat, 26 Oct 2013 11:24:13 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Mobile]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Softwares]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Technology]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Android 4.3]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Galaxy S4]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Jellybean]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=797</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/android-4-3-update-for-samsung-galaxy-s4"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-02-01-168x300.png" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-02-01" title="" /></a>When Google announced the minor update to its mobile operating system (Android 4.3) months ago, millions of enthusiasts were thrilled and excited to get hands of the new software version. As usual, the Nexus users were the first ones to have their devices get the taste of the new Jellybean-flavored operating system. Along with them are the users of the Google Play edition of two of the most popular Android devices released in 2013  - HTC&#8217;s One and Samsung&#8217;s Galaxy[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-02-01.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-798" alt="Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-02-01" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-02-01-168x300.png" width="168" height="300" /></a></p>
<p>When Google announced the minor update to its mobile operating system (Android 4.3) months ago, millions of enthusiasts were thrilled and excited to get hands of the new software version. As usual, the Nexus users were the first ones to have their devices get the taste of the new Jellybean-flavored operating system. Along with them are the users of the Google Play edition of two of the most popular Android devices released in 2013  - HTC&#8217;s One and Samsung&#8217;s Galaxy S4.</p>
<p>Normally, it takes a while for OEMs to roll out software updates as they need to make  necessary tweaks for their UI layer and other stock applications to work as seamlessly as possible with the new software version. This is no exception for the best selling Android device just yet &#8211; Galaxy S4 that Samsung recently announced it already breached 40 million mark. Released in April 2013, the mighty device comes with Android 4.2.2 Jellybean out of the box and packs with generous amount of premium features and the latest version of TouchWiz &#8211; Samsung&#8217;s proprietary Android skin.</p>
<p><strong>First major update</strong><br />
The jump from Android 4.2.2 to 4.3 marks the S4&#8242;s first major firmware upgrade although the update itself is just a minor release. Being Samsung&#8217;s flagship Android smartphone to date, it is the first one to receive the new firmware update joining the recently launched Galaxy Note 3 which comes with Android 4.3 by default.</p>
<p><strong>What to expect?</strong><br />
With Android 4.3, Samsung managed to include optimizations, update to it&#8217;s own applications and brand new applications to the Galaxy S4. The device is now compatible with Galaxy Gear &#8211; Samsung&#8217;s first smartwatch again, joining the Galaxy Note 3 which is the only device compatible with the smartwatch at the time of release.  Below is the complete  list of changes* in the software update:</p>
<ul>
<li><span style="line-height: 13px;">OpenGL 3.0 Support<br />
</span></li>
<li>GALAXY GEAR Support</li>
<li>TRIM Support (Makes the device much faster)</li>
<li>ANT+ Support</li>
<li>Samsung KNOX Implementation (KNOX bootloader and dedicated application)</li>
<li>Samsung Wallet comes pre-loaded</li>
<li>Improved RAM management</li>
<li> Improved Display colour reproduction (Display looks much sharper than before)</li>
<li>Improved TouchWiz Launcher (Much less launcher redraws and less lag)</li>
<li>New Samsung Keyboard</li>
<li>New Samsung Browser (Full screen by default, new tab interface and more)</li>
<li>New Reading Mode (Optimises display for reading, used by only a few specific applications)</li>
<li>New Camera firmware</li>
<li>Minor UI tweaks (Contacts app, Flashlight Widget, dialog boxes etc)</li>
</ul>
<p><small>* Sammobile</small></p>
<p><strong>Gallery</strong></p>
<p><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-10-13.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-806 alignnone" alt="Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-10-13" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-10-13-168x300.png" width="168" height="300" /></a> <a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-10-54.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-807 alignnone" alt="Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-10-54" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-10-54-168x300.png" width="168" height="300" /></a> <a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-09-44.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-805 alignnone" alt="Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-09-44" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-09-44-168x300.png" width="168" height="300" /></a> <a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-08-53.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-803 alignnone" alt="Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-08-53" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-08-53-168x300.png" width="168" height="300" /></a> <a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-05-39.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-802 alignnone" alt="Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-05-39" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-05-39-168x300.png" width="168" height="300" /></a> <a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-04-31.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-801 alignnone" alt="Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-04-31" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-04-31-168x300.png" width="168" height="300" /></a> <a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-03-49.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-800 alignnone" alt="Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-03-49" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-03-49-168x300.png" width="168" height="300" /></a> <a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-02-59.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-799 alignnone" alt="Samsung Galaxy S4 Android 4.3" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-02-59-168x300.png" width="168" height="300" /></a><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-09-071.png"><img class="size-medium wp-image-815 alignnone" alt="Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-09-07" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screenshot_2013-10-26-19-09-071-300x168.png" width="300" height="168" /></a></p>
