		<title>Safari Facebook Session Issue</title>
		<link>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/safari-facebook-session-issue</link>
		<comments>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/safari-facebook-session-issue#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 02 May 2013 16:18:50 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Softwares]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Technology]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[facebook application]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Safari]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=773</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/safari-facebook-session-issue"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" height="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Apple-Safari-150x150.png" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="" title="" /></a>One of the common issues web developers encounter in developing Facebook applications is loosing session. This leads the application to redirect to the login url, request for and regenerate a new token and redirects back to the application url. In the case of IE (Internet Explorer), this issue can be addressed simply by setting P3P header. Please click here to read related story. For Safari, however, setting PHP header is not enough. Chances are, the application keeps coming back to[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img class="aligncenter" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Apple-Safari.png" alt="" width="256" height="256" /></p>
<p>One of the common issues web developers encounter in developing Facebook applications is loosing session. This leads the application to redirect to the login url, request for and regenerate a new token and redirects back to the application url. In the case of IE (Internet Explorer), this issue can be addressed simply by setting P3P header. Please click <a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/php-snippets-resolving-ie-facebook-session-issue">here</a> to read related story.  For Safari, however, setting PHP header is not enough. Chances are, the application keeps coming back to the index page regardless of the page that links are pointing to.</p>
<p><strong>The Experience</strong></p>
<p>I have been working for a page tab app and was surprised when our QA specialist informed me that not a single link is working in Safari. Spent hours looking for a fix online in the hope that other developers encountered the same problem in the past and were able to resolve it. Tons of answers were given, unfortunately though, none of them seems working. Code modifications here and there were made but none of the posted solutions seem to work for me.</p>
<p><strong>The Solution</strong></p>
<p>The fix that works for my application doesn&#8217;t involve coding at all. It&#8217;s all in the browser settings. Here&#8217;s how:</p>
<p>Click Settings icon and click Preferences</p>
<p><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/settings.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-774" title="Settings" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/settings-231x300.jpg" alt="" width="231" height="300" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>A popup dialog box will appear just like the one below:</p>
<p><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/settings1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-775" title="General" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/settings1-300x232.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="232" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Click Privacy tab</p>
<p><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/settings2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-776" title="Privacy" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/settings2-300x153.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="153" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Under Block Cookies, check Never</p>
<p><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/settings3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-777" title="Block cookies" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/settings3-300x155.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="155" /></a></p>
<fb:like href=http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/safari-facebook-session-issue font=></fb:like>]]></content:encoded>
