		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=750</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/how-to-install-jelly-bean-on-your-samsung-galaxy-s"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Screenshot_2012-08-08-09-51-31-180x300.png" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="" title="Screenshot_2012-08-08-09-51-31" /></a>Team Android Jelly Bean (TAJB) recently released the latest Jelly Bean build for the old but mighty Samsung Galaxy S.  V7.1 which was made public on August 5th fixes some issues from the previous versions.  The authors claim that almost everything now works with this revision, I decided to give my very own GT-19000  a taste of Jelly Bean. If your device is already rooted just as I do when I flashed ICS on mine, you just need to proceed[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Screenshot_2012-08-08-09-51-31.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-751" title="Screenshot_2012-08-08-09-51-31" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Screenshot_2012-08-08-09-51-31-180x300.png" alt="" width="180" height="300" /></a></p>
<p>Team Android Jelly Bean (TAJB) recently released the latest Jelly Bean build for the old but mighty Samsung Galaxy S.  V7.1 which was made public on August 5th fixes some issues from the previous versions.  The authors claim that almost everything now works with this revision, I decided to give my very own GT-19000  a taste of Jelly Bean.</p>
<p>If your device is already rooted just as I do when I <a title="How to install ICS on your Galaxy S" href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/how-to-install-ics-on-your-samsunggalaxy-s">flashed ICS on mine</a>, you just need to proceed as follows: (Warning:  before proceeding, make the necessary backup of your data(SMS, contacts, apps, etc.))</p>
<ol>
<li>Download the TAJB build <a href="http://teamjellybean.noez.in/" target="_blank">here</a>. This is more or less 200MB of zip file.</li>
<li>Save the zip file on your sd card.</li>
<li>Using CWM, wipe data/factory reset.</li>
<li>Wipe cache.</li>
<li>Go to Advanced &gt; Wipe Dalvik cache.</li>
<li>Go back to main menu.</li>
<li>Go to &#8220;Install zip from sd card&#8221; then select &#8220;choose zip from sd card&#8221;</li>
<li>Wait until the installation of the new ROM is complete.</li>
<li>Go to Advanced &gt; Fix Permissions</li>
<li>Reboot your device.</li>
</ol>
<div>To give you a glimpse of what your device will look like after the installation, here it is:</div>
<div>

<a href='http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/how-to-install-jelly-bean-on-your-samsung-galaxy-s/screenshot_2012-08-08-09-52-47'><img width="150" height="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Screenshot_2012-08-08-09-52-47-150x150.png" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Screenshot_2012-08-08-09-52-47" /></a>
