		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=747</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/google-introduces-jelly-bean"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" height="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/android_logo-150x150.gif" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="" title="Android" /></a>Google recently unveiled Android 4.1 dubbed as Jelly Bean which is the next version of the most popular mobile operating system. &#8220;The fastest and smoothest version of Android yet&#8221;, as what the search giant claims the platform to be, Jelly Bean is packed with UI enhancements from the mighty Ice Cream Sandwich (Android 4.0), software updates and exciting new features for your Android devices. What to Expect? Faster, smoother and more responsive than ICS Expandable and actionable notifications Widgets work[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/android_logo-300x225.gif"><img class="aligncenter" title="Android" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/android_logo-300x225.gif" alt="" width="300" height="225" /></a></p>
<p>Google recently unveiled Android 4.1 dubbed as Jelly Bean which is the next version of the most popular mobile operating system. &#8220;The fastest and smoothest version of Android yet&#8221;, as what the search giant claims the platform to be, Jelly Bean is packed with UI enhancements from the mighty Ice Cream Sandwich (Android 4.0), software updates and exciting new features for your Android devices.</p>
<p><strong>What to Expect?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Faster, smoother and more responsive than ICS</li>
<li>Expandable and actionable notifications</li>
<li>Widgets work smarter as they resize on their own to fit in the available homescreen space</li>
<li>Taking and sharing photos are made even more easier</li>
<li>Android&#8217;s dictionaries are made more accurate and text-to-speech capabilities are improved as well</li>
<li>&#8216;Gesture Mode&#8217; makes it possible for blind people to navigate the UI</li>
<li>Share files, contacts, links and other important documents to your friends by just tapping your NFC-enabled Android devices together, thanks to Android Beam</li>
<li>Jelly Bean redefines search experience with a fresh new look and feel</li>
<li>Search the web using your voice through Voice Search</li>
<li>Android 4.1 introduces  a cool new feature called Google Now which brings you the right information just at the right time</li>
</ul>
<div>Here&#8217;s a video showing a comparison between Jelly Bean screen transition and Ice Cream Sandwich&#8217;s:</div>
<p><iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/V5E5revikUU" frameborder="0" width="560" height="315"></iframe></p>
<fb:like href=http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/google-introduces-jelly-bean font=></fb:like>]]></content:encoded>
