		<title>How to add app to your Facebook page</title>
		<link>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/how-to-add-app-to-your-facebook-page</link>
		<comments>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/how-to-add-app-to-your-facebook-page#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Sun, 22 Jan 2012 03:26:45 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Web]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[custom tab]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[facebook]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[facebook application]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[facebook fan page]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=691</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/how-to-add-app-to-your-facebook-page"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/facebook-apps-150x150.jpg" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="" title="Facebook Application" /></a>&#160; Facebook application profile pages provide a convenient way of adding custom tabs to your Facebook fan pages simply by clicking on the &#8216;Add to my page&#8217; link on the left rail. Recently, however, the social networking giant announced that it will be deleting all app profile pages and redirecting all traffic on the application itself by February 1, 2012. Please refer to Facebook Developer Roadmap for more information. Such move now requires all fan page administrators and developers to[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter" title="Facebook Application" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/facebook-apps-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></p>
<p>Facebook application profile pages provide a convenient way of adding custom tabs to your Facebook fan pages simply by clicking on the &#8216;Add to my page&#8217; link on the left rail. Recently, however, the social networking giant announced that it will be deleting all app profile pages and redirecting all traffic on the application itself by February 1, 2012. Please refer to Facebook <a title="Developer Roadmap" href="https://developers.facebook.com/roadmap/" target="_blank">Developer Roadmap</a> for more information. Such move now requires all fan page administrators and developers to find an alternative way of adding app to pages.</p>
<p>Now that Facebook is removing profile app pages, here&#8217;s an alternative way of adding application to your fan page.  This time, Facebook fan page administrators need to go explicitly navigating on the following URL to add an app to their pages:</p>
<p><strong>https://www.facebook.com/dialog/pagetab?app_id=YOUR_APP_ID&amp;next=YOUR_URL</strong></p>
<p>YOUR_APP_ID and YOUR_URL can both be found in the app settings.</p>
<p>Below is a sample resulting screen:</p>
<p><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/add-page-tab.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-692" title="add-page-tab" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/add-page-tab-300x115.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="115" /></a></p>
<fb:like href=http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/how-to-add-app-to-your-facebook-page font=></fb:like>]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/how-to-add-app-to-your-facebook-page/feed</wfw:commentRss>
