		<title>Google+ now available in iTunes</title>
		<link>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/google-now-available-in-itunes</link>
		<comments>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/google-now-available-in-itunes#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Fri, 22 Jul 2011 15:22:37 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Mobile]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Web]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Google]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Goolge+]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[iOS]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[iPad]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[iPhone]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[iPod]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[iTunes]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=585</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/google-now-available-in-itunes"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" height="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/google-plus-logo-150x150.jpg" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="" title="google-plus-logo" /></a>The new and fast-growing social networking service from Google releases its iOS application in the iTunes Store. Google+, initially released as a native application exclusively for Android users now has its counterpart running on Apple&#8217;s iOS for US Store for now. Features  Some of the features included in the Google+ mobile application for iOS are the following: Circles which let you share the right things with just the right people. Stream, where you can get updates from your circles or[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a title="Google+" href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/google-plus-logo.jpg" rel="lightbox"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-586" title="google-plus-logo" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/google-plus-logo.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="168" /></a></p>
<p>The new and fast-growing social networking service from Google releases its iOS application in the iTunes Store. Google+, initially released as a native application exclusively for Android users now has its counterpart running on Apple&#8217;s iOS for US Store for now.</p>
<p><strong>Features </strong></p>
<p>Some of the features included in the Google+ mobile application for iOS are the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>Circles which let you share the right things with just the right people.</li>
<li>Stream, where you can get updates from your circles or see what people are saying about things nearby.</li>
<li>Huddle, super-fast group messaging for everyone in your circles.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Big disappointment to iPod Touch users</strong></p>
<p>Although Google+ for iOS runs on the same platform as the iPad and iPhone, the application will not work on iPod touch which is also an iOS device. Reviews came in the application profile page in iTunes store expressing disappointment to Google for not having support for iPod touch. Some of them are the following:</p>
<p>&#8220;Seriously, how hard is it to have iPod touch support? Its the same OS! Its WI-FI! Wake up!!! &#8221; &#8211; Brandon Zanan</p>
<p>&#8220;&#8230; I&#8217;m really enjoying the new Google+ social networking concept, and when I heard it was available for download via the app store I went right to it. Sad thing is, I have one of the 2nd generation iPod Touches and it is not supported for the application. Just thought I&#8217;d spread the word.&#8221; &#8211; Christopher Reynolds</p>
<p>&#8220;Just like the title says (Doesn&#8217;t support the iPod Touch), this application won&#8217;t run on an iPod Touch. Come on, Google!&#8221; &#8211; Andreas Yankopolus</p>
<p>Google+ for iOS 5.3 MB in file size and is strictly available for users 18 years old and above.</p>
<fb:like href=http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/google-now-available-in-itunes font=></fb:like>]]></content:encoded>
