		<title>Apple introduces iTunes in the Cloud Beta</title>
		<link>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/apple-introduces-itunes-in-the-cloud-beta</link>
		<comments>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/apple-introduces-itunes-in-the-cloud-beta#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Mon, 13 Jun 2011 00:37:36 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Mobile]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Softwares]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Technology]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[iPad]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[iPhone]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[iPod]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[iTunes]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=548</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/apple-introduces-itunes-in-the-cloud-beta"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" height="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/itunes-150x150.jpg" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="" title="iTunes" /></a>iTunes by Apple received a software update recently which introduces the digital music jukebox in the Cloud Beta weeks after the release of iTunes 10.2.2 and several days after the consumer electronics company reveals features of the iOS 5. Now on its 10.3.1 version, iTunes contains the following new features: The music you purchase in iTunes appears automatically on all your devices. Purchase music from any device or computer and automatically download a copy to your PC and iOS devices.[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="iTunes" rel="lightbox" href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/itunes.jpg"><img class="aligncenter" title="iTunes" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/itunes.jpg" alt="" width="225" height="225" /></a></p>
<p>iTunes by Apple received a software update recently which introduces the digital music jukebox in the Cloud Beta weeks after the release of <a href="../itunes-10-2-2-software-update" target="_blank">iTunes 10.2.2</a> and several days after the consumer electronics company reveals features of the <a href="../apple-reveals-ios-5-features">iOS 5</a>. Now on its 10.3.1 version, iTunes contains the following new features:</p>
<ul>
<li>The music you purchase in iTunes appears automatically on all your devices. Purchase music from any device or computer and automatically download a copy to your PC and iOS devices.</li>
<li>You can also download your past iTunes purchases. Where you want, when you want. Download your past music purchases again at no additional cost. Your purchases are available in the iTunes Store on your PC or in the iTunes app on your iPhone, iPad, or iPod touch. Previous purchases may be unavailable if they are no longer on the iTunes Store.</li>
<li>Add Books to the iTunes Store. Discover and buy your favorite books on your computer and automatically download them to iBooks on your iPhone, iPad, or iPod touch. This version also allows you to use Automatic Downloads with apps and books or download previously purchased apps and books from your computer or iOS device.</li>
</ul>
<p>iTunes 10.3.1 is about 65MB in file size.</p>
<p>For information on the security content of this update, please visit: <a href="http://support.apple.com/kb/HT1222" target="_blank">support.apple.com/kb/HT1222</a></p>
