		<title>Mac OS X Lion features unveiled</title>
		<link>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/new-mac-os-x-lion-features-unveiled</link>
		<comments>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/new-mac-os-x-lion-features-unveiled#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 09 Jun 2011 00:21:53 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Softwares]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Technology]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Mac]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Mac OS X Lion]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[operating system]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[WWDC]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=519</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/new-mac-os-x-lion-features-unveiled"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" height="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Mac-OS-X-Lion-150x150.jpg" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="" title="Mac-OS-X-Lion" /></a>Aside from the iOS 5 features being revealed in the Apple Worldwide Developers Conference (WWDC) in San Fransciso, the consumer electronics company also highlights the upcoming Mac OS X Lion in the event. (Click here to read related story)  Phil Schiller, SVP for WW Product Marketing, together with Craig Federighi, VP for OS X Software, talks about and demos the new features Mac OS users can look forward to in the new operating system. Some of the features include the[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Mac-OS-X-Lion.jpg" rel="lightbox" title="Mac OS X Lion"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-520" title="Mac-OS-X-Lion" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/Mac-OS-X-Lion.jpg" alt="" width="260" height="194" /></a></p>
<p>Aside from the iOS 5 features being revealed in the Apple Worldwide Developers Conference (WWDC) in San Fransciso, the consumer electronics company also highlights the upcoming Mac OS X Lion in the event. (Click <a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/apple-reveals-ios-5-features">here </a>to read related story)  Phil Schiller, SVP for WW Product Marketing, together with Craig Federighi, VP for OS X Software, talks about and demos the new features Mac OS users can look forward to in the new operating system. Some of the features include the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>Multi-touch gestures</li>
<li>Full-screen applications</li>
<li>Mission control</li>
<li>Mac App Store that&#8217;s made built-in in Mac OS X Lion, supports in-app purchase with push notification, sandboxing and delta updates</li>
<li>Launchpad</li>
<li>Resume feature which lets you get back to where you were exactly</li>
<li>Auto save</li>
<li>Versions</li>
<li>Airdrop, a peer-to-peer WiFi network solution with auto discovery and setup, confirmation to send and receive with data encryption for security</li>
<li>Mail with conversation view, snippets, search token and favorites bar</li>
</ul>
<p>Aside from the key features mentioned above, Mac OS X Lion also comes with exciting new features like Windows migration, Filevault, Facetime, Safari reading list and more.</p>
<p>The size of the software is about 4GB which can be downloaded in Mac App Store for a surprising $29.99 price and will be available in July.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
