		<title>Apple reveals iOS 5 features</title>
		<link>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/apple-reveals-ios-5-features</link>
		<comments>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/apple-reveals-ios-5-features#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Tue, 07 Jun 2011 23:26:57 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Mobile]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Softwares]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Technology]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[iOS]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[iOS 5]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Scott Forstall]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[WWDC]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=510</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/apple-reveals-ios-5-features"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" height="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/hero20110302-150x150.jpg" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="" title="iOS" /></a>In the Apple Worldwide Developers Conference (WWDC) held recently, Scott Forstall (SVP for iOS Software) reveals the latest features of the upcoming new version of one of the most popular mobile operating system &#8211; the iOS 5. Forstall talks about 10 of the 250 new features of iOS which includes the following: Notifications. iOS 5 comes with notification center which combines all of the device&#8217;s notifications in one place. More information is also provided on the lock screen and you[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="iOS" rel="lightbox" href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/hero20110302-300x85.jpg"><img class="aligncenter" title="iOS" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/hero20110302-300x85.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="85" /></a></p>
<p>In the Apple Worldwide Developers Conference (WWDC) held recently, Scott Forstall (SVP for iOS Software) reveals the latest features of the upcoming new version of one of the most popular mobile operating system &#8211; the iOS 5. Forstall talks about 10 of the 250 new features of iOS which includes the following:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Notifications</strong>. iOS 5 comes with <em>notification center</em> which combines all of the device&#8217;s notifications in one place. More information is also provided on the lock screen and you can now directly go to the application associated with the notification just by swiping your finger with an added convenience since notifications don&#8217;t interrupt anymore.</li>
<li><strong>Newsstand</strong>. This combines all known and international newspapers and magazines in one place. With subscription and background download features, you can have the latest issues of the newspapers and magazines automatically on you iOS device.</li>
<li><strong>Twitter Integration</strong>. Apple integrates the social microblogging application the new iOS within the device&#8217;s camera and Safari. Contacts integration automatically updates photos in your contact list if they&#8217;re available on Twitter.</li>
<li><strong>Enhanced Safari</strong>.  Safari in iOS 5 now supports full-tabbed browsing so you can switch from one page to another easily. The browser also comes with <em>reading list </em>where you can bookmark pages for later reading.</li>
<li><strong>Reminders</strong>. iOS 5 lets you store reminders including dates and locations which can be synched with iCal and Microsoft Exchange.</li>
<li><strong>New Camera Features</strong>. Here are some of the new things that can be done with the device&#8217;s camera running iOS 5:
<ul>
<li>A new camera shortcut icon is added on the lock screen which lets you take a photo immediately</li>
<li>The volume up key may now be used to take photos</li>
<li>Grid lines are added</li>
<li>You can pinch to zoom from the camera</li>
<li>AE/AF lock</li>
<li>Editing photo is now possible including crop, rotate and red-eye reduction</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>New Mail Features</strong>. The mail client for iOS 5 comes with rich text formatting, indentation control, draggable adddresses, flag messages, search entire message, swipe to inbox for iPads and S/MIME support.</li>
<li><strong>PC free</strong>. Getting started with iOS 5 doesn&#8217;t require a PC. Software updates and Delta updates can be done over-the-air.</li>
<li><strong>Improved Game Center</strong>. The Game Center has new features including photos, achievement points, friend discovery, game discovery, game downloads and turn-based games.</li>
<li><strong>iMessage</strong>. Apple introduces the new messaging service that works accross iOS device users &#8211; iMessage. iMessage has the following features:
<ul>
<li>Be able to send text, photos, videos, contacts and group messages among iOS users</li>
<li>delivery receipts</li>
<li>read receipts</li>
<li>typing indication</li>
<li>3G + WiFi support</li>
<li>messages are encrypted for security</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>To compliment all these exciting new iOS 5 features are airplay mirroring, wifi sync to itunes and multitasking gestures to name a few. New developer tools, newsstand kit, core image and UI customization are also provided for iOS developers.</p>
<p>iOS 5 will be made available for the following devices:</p>
<ul>
<li>iPhone 3GS and iPhone 4</li>
<li>iPad and iPad 2</li>
<li>iPod touch (3rd and 4th generation)</li>
</ul>
