		<title>PHP Snippets: Publishing story on a Facebook wall</title>
		<link>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/php-snippets-publishing-story-on-a-facebook-wall</link>
		<comments>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/php-snippets-publishing-story-on-a-facebook-wall#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Tue, 07 Jun 2011 00:23:22 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Web]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[facebook]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[facebook application]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[PHP]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[PHP Snippets]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=508</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/php-snippets-publishing-story-on-a-facebook-wall"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/php.png" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="" title="PHP" /></a>Publishing story on a Facebook user&#8217;s wall, or simply post to wall,  is the most common way of sharing over the social networking site. This is visible to all users connected with the one posting the story so it is sometimes used to promote a website link (click here to read related post), a Facebook application, photos, or sometimes share a note. Post to wall functionality within a Facebook application is a nice-to-have to spread it among Facebook users. The[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/facebook-apps.jpg"></a><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/php.png"><img class="aligncenter" title="PHP" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/php.png" alt="" width="184" height="113" /></a></p>
<p>Publishing story on a Facebook user&#8217;s wall, or simply post to wall,  is the most common way of sharing over the social networking site. This is visible to all users connected with the one posting the story so it is sometimes used to promote a website link (click <a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/adding-thumbnail-title-and-description-in-sharing-links-on-facebook">here</a> to read related post), a Facebook application, photos, or sometimes share a note.</p>
<p>Post to wall functionality within a Facebook application is a nice-to-have to spread it among Facebook users. The code snippet below demonstrates how to publish story on a Facebook wall.</p>
<pre><code>function post_to_wall($facebook, $token, $message, $photo, $link, $title, $desc, $to_fbid = false) {
 if(!$to_fbid) {
    $to = 'me';
 } else {
    $to = $to_fbid;
 }

 try {
    $post = $facebook-&gt;api('/' . $to . '/feed/',
       'post',
       array('access_token'     =&gt; $token,
             'message'             =&gt; $message,
             'picture'            =&gt; $photo,
             'link'                =&gt; $link,
             'name'                =&gt; $title,
             'description'        =&gt; $desc));
 } catch(FacebookApiException $e) {
    return 0;
 }
    return 1;
}</code></pre>
<p>Sample usage:</p>
<pre><code>//include Facebook PHP SDK
include_once('facebook.php');

 // Create instance of the Facebook class
 $facebook = new Facebook(array('appId'  =&gt; 'YOUR APPLICATION ID',
                                'secret' =&gt; 'YOUR APPLICATION SECRET KEY',
                                'cookie' =&gt; true,));

 // Facebook Authentication
 $session    = $facebook-&gt;getSession();
 $login_url  = $facebook-&gt;getLoginUrl(array('canvas'    =&gt; 1,
                                            'fbconnect' =&gt; 0,
                                            'req_perms' =&gt; 'publish_stream'));

 if(!$session) {
    echo "&lt;script type='text/javascript'&gt;top.location.href = '" . $login_url . "';&lt;/script&gt;";
    exit;
 } else {
    try {
       $uid    = $facebook-&gt;getUser();
       $fbme    = $facebook-&gt;api('/me');
    } catch (FacebookApiException $e) {
       echo "&lt;script type='text/javascript'&gt;top.location.href = '" . $login_url . "';&lt;/script&gt;";
       exit;
    }
 }

$message    = '';
$photo      = 'path_to_your_photo.jpg';
$title      = 'YOUR TITLE';
$link       = 'http://yourdomain.com ';
$desc       = 'This is a sample story';

$post = post_to_wall($facebook, $session['access_token'], $message, $photo, $link, $title, $desc);</code></pre>
<p>If you want to post to a specific Facebook user&#8217;s wall, you may pass the Facebook user id of that user to the $to_fbid</p>
<pre><code>$post = post_to_wall($facebook, $session['access_token'], $message, $photo, $link, $title, $desc, '1234567');</code></pre>
<fb:like href=http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/php-snippets-publishing-story-on-a-facebook-wall font=></fb:like>]]></content:encoded>
