		<title>Adding social plugins to your site</title>
		<link>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/adding-social-plugins-to-your-site</link>
		<comments>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/adding-social-plugins-to-your-site#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Mon, 06 Jun 2011 00:42:39 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Web]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[facebook]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[social plugins]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=504</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/adding-social-plugins-to-your-site"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" height="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/facebook-apps-150x150.jpg" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="" title="Facebook" /></a>Social plugins are Facebook extensions that enable web developers provide social experiences to their users as they let users see their friends&#8217; social activities including likes, comments, etc. Facebook provides an array of social plugins for developers to choose from which includes the following: Like Button &#8211; lets users share pages from your site back to their Facebook profile with one click Send Button &#8211; allows your users to easily send your content to their friends Comments &#8211; lets users[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="Facebook" rel="lightbox" href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/facebook-apps.jpg"><img class="aligncenter" title="Facebook" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/facebook-apps.jpg" alt="" width="225" height="225" /></a></p>
<p>Social plugins are Facebook extensions that enable web developers provide social experiences to their users as they let users see their friends&#8217; social activities including likes, comments, etc. Facebook provides an array of social plugins for developers to choose from which includes the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>Like Button &#8211; lets users share pages from your site back to their Facebook profile with one click</li>
<li>Send Button &#8211; allows your users to easily send your content to their friends</li>
<li>Comments &#8211; lets users comment on any piece of content on your site</li>
<li>Activity Feed &#8211;  shows users what their friends are doing on your site through likes and comments</li>
<li>Recommendations &#8211; gives users personalized suggestions for pages on your site they might like</li>
<li>Like Box &#8211;  enables users to like your Facebook Page and view its stream directly from your website</li>
<li>Login Button &#8211; shows profile pictures of the user&#8217;s friends who have already signed up for your site in addition to a login button</li>
<li>Registration &#8211; allows users to easily sign up for your website with their Facebook account</li>
<li>Facepile &#8211; displays the Facebook profile pictures of users who have liked your page or have signed up for your site</li>
<li>Live Stream &#8211; lets your users share activity and comments in real-time as they interact during a live event</li>
</ul>
<p>Codes for a specific social plugin are provided in Facebook&#8217;s <a title="Social Plugin - Facebook Developers" href="http://developers.facebook.com/docs/plugins/" target="_blank">Social Plugin </a>documentation page including options to fit your site&#8217;s social needs.</p>
<div id="_mcePaste" class="mcePaste" style="position: absolute; left: -10000px; top: 0px; width: 1px; height: 1px; overflow: hidden;">
<table class="uiGrid" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
<div class="plugin clearfix">
<div class="thumbnail"><a href="http://developers.facebook.com/docs/reference/plugins/send"><img class="img" src="http://developers.facebook.com/attachment/send.png" alt="" width="128" height="88" /></a></div>
<div class="name"><a href="http://developers.facebook.com/docs/reference/plugins/send">Send Button</a></div>
<div class="desc">
<p>The Send Button allows your users to easily send your content to their friends.</p>
</div>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<fb:like href=http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/adding-social-plugins-to-your-site font=></fb:like>]]></content:encoded>
