		<title>How to get Facebook fanpage likes count</title>
		<link>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/how-to-get-facebook-fan-count</link>
		<comments>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/how-to-get-facebook-fan-count#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 02 Jun 2011 00:53:56 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Web]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[facebook]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[facebook application]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[facebook fan count]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[facebook fan page]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=478</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/how-to-get-facebook-fan-count"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" height="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/facebook-apps-150x150.jpg" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="" title="Facebook Application" /></a>It&#8217;s no question that social media invades the world wide web in terms of popularity. It has become a powerful tool for the known people to let their fans know more about them, for the advertisers to expose more of their products and services, and so on. Truly, online marketers&#8217; weapon of choice is social media. Facebook fan page is the most common social media tool used nowadays by various sectors. To increase the fans or the number of Facebook[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="Facebook Application" rel="lightbox" href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/facebook-apps.jpg"><img class="aligncenter" title="Facebook Application" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/facebook-apps.jpg" alt="" width="225" height="225" /></a></p>
<p>It&#8217;s no question that social media invades the world wide web in terms of popularity. It has become a powerful tool for the known people to let their fans know more about them, for the advertisers to expose more of their products and services, and so on. Truly, online marketers&#8217; weapon of choice is social media.</p>
<p>Facebook fan page is the most common social media tool used nowadays by various sectors. To increase the fans or the number of Facebook users who has &#8220;liked&#8221; it is every Facebook fan page owners&#8217; aim. It may not be that useful to show or publish your fan count if you haven&#8217;t got that significant amount but as soon as you reach that high, isn&#8217;t it a good idea to let your fans know that there are other Facebook users out there that they share the same interest with?</p>
<p>Counting the fan count of a Facebook page is simple if you are familiar with Facebook API. It only requires an FQL (Facebook Query Language) to retrieve the count of a particular fan page. The code snippet shows how to do it:</p>
<pre><code>&lt;?php

require_once('facebook.php');

$facebook = new Facebook(array(
 'appId'  =&gt; 'your_app_id',
 'secret' =&gt; 'your_app_secret',
 'cookie' =&gt; true,
));

$result = $facebook-&gt;api(array(
 'method' =&gt; 'fql.query',
 'query' =&gt; 'select fan_count from page where page_id = your_page_id;'
));

$fb_fans = $result[0]['fan_count'];

?&gt;</code></pre>
<p>You just need to download and include the <a href="https://github.com/facebook/php-sdk/" target="_blank">Facebook PHP SDK</a>, create an instance of the Facebook class and make an FQL query. That&#8217;s how simple it is to count your fans from an application.</p>
<fb:like href=http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/how-to-get-facebook-fan-count font=></fb:like>]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/how-to-get-facebook-fan-count/feed</wfw:commentRss>
