		<title>How to get your IP details</title>
		<link>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/how-to-get-your-ip-details</link>
		<comments>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/how-to-get-your-ip-details#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Sun, 22 May 2011 00:37:36 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Technology]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Web]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[dynamic IP]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[IP]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[IP address]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[IP address details]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[IP-details.com]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[static IP]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=427</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/how-to-get-your-ip-details"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" height="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/plugins/thumbnail-for-excerpts/tfe_no_thumb.png" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="" title="" /></a>What is an IP address? An Internet Protocol address (IP address) is a numerical label assigned to each device (e.g., computer, printer) participating in a computer network that uses the Internet Protocol for communication. An IP address serves two principal functions: host or network interface identification and location addressing. Its role has been characterized as follows: &#8220;A name indicates what we seek. An address indicates where it is. A route indicates how to get there. (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IP_address) IP address assignment Internet[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong>What is an IP address?</strong></p>
<p>An Internet Protocol address (IP address) is a numerical label assigned to each device (e.g., computer, printer) participating in a computer network that uses the Internet Protocol for communication. An IP address serves two principal functions: host or network interface identification and location addressing. Its role has been characterized as follows: &#8220;A name indicates what we seek. An address indicates where it is. A route indicates how to get there. (<em>http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IP_address</em>)</p>
<p><strong>IP address assignment</strong></p>
<p>Internet Protocol addresses be either static or dynamic. Static IP address is an IP address that is permanently assigned to a host by fixed configuration of its hardware or software, also referred to as persistent configuration. Dynamic IP address, on the other hand, is an IP address assigned to a host anew at the time of booting.</p>
<p><strong>Your IP address details</strong></p>
<p>A number of websites offer online utility that gets the Internet Protocol address you are currently assigned with. IP-details.com (http://ip-details.com) for example gives you wealth of information that has something to do with your IP address including Internet Service Provider (ISP), IP location, country, coordinates, and so on. On a Local Area Network (LAN), you can get your IP address by issuing <em>ipconfig</em> command on the command prompt if you&#8217;re using a PC.</p>
<fb:like href=http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/how-to-get-your-ip-details font=></fb:like>]]></content:encoded>
