		<title>No message alerts on your Nokia phone?</title>
		<link>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/no-message-alerts-on-your-nokia-phone</link>
		<comments>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/no-message-alerts-on-your-nokia-phone#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Sun, 15 May 2011 05:25:59 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Mobile]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Nokia]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Nokia E72]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Symbian OS]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=351</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/no-message-alerts-on-your-nokia-phone"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Nokia-E72-620x457-300x221.jpg" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="" title="Nokia-E72-620x457" /></a>Have you been receiving messages lately on your Nokia phone but your device doesn&#8217;t alert you? Do you need to keep looking on your phone from time to time just to make sure you don&#8217;t miss replying a single message right away because you have to? I once experience this before on my Nokia E72. I never had problem with my device before until it suddenly stops giving an alert when I receive messages. Since then, my only clue that[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Nokia-E72-620x457.jpg" rel="lightbox" title="Nokia E72"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-39" title="Nokia-E72-620x457" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Nokia-E72-620x457-300x221.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="221" /></a></p>
<p>Have you been receiving messages lately on your Nokia phone but your device doesn&#8217;t alert you? Do you need to keep looking on your phone from time to time just to make sure you don&#8217;t miss replying a single message right away because you have to?</p>
<p>I once experience this before on my Nokia E72. I never had problem with my device before until it suddenly stops giving an alert when I receive messages. Since then, my only clue that I have a new message to read is the blinking light on the device&#8217;s optical navi® key. The main disadvantage of this for me is that I, most of the time, fail to reply back to the messages right away.</p>
<p><strong>The Solution</strong><br />
To get rid of the hassle the problem is bringing me everyday, I searched for a possible cause of it in the Nokia forums and discussions over the net until I found one that seems to be credible.  The &#8220;saver-of-the-day&#8221; says it happens when the number of messages in the inbox folder of the devices reaches 2000. As a solution, users must remove the messages out of that folder &#8211; you can delete it or take it somewhere else (e.g., create a folder say &#8216;archives&#8217;) if you want to keep those. After clearing the inbox, you may need to restart your phone.</p>
<p>The &#8220;practically unlimited&#8221; number of messages that Nokia phones can handle is not really unlimited after apparently because the device suddenly stops some of its features when it reaches a certain threshold.</p>
<fb:like href=http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/no-message-alerts-on-your-nokia-phone font=></fb:like>]]></content:encoded>
