		<title>Changing author or publish scheduled post in WordPress</title>
		<link>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/changing-author-post-status-in-wordpress</link>
		<comments>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/changing-author-post-status-in-wordpress#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Sat, 14 May 2011 09:54:18 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Web]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[blogging tool]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[publishing platform]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Wordpress]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=328</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/changing-author-post-status-in-wordpress"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" height="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/wordpress-150x150.jpg" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="" title="wordpress" /></a>WordPress, one of the most popular blogging tool and publishing platform provides endless ways for bloggers to edit some minor details of their posts. It&#8217;s just a matter of exploring wp-admin page. I must admit that I, myself, once had trouble looking for a button, a link or something that will let me change the author of a particular post. It took me minutes navigating the admin page with no luck until a dropdown that says &#8216;Bulk Actions&#8217; on the[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/wordpress.jpg" rel="lightbox" title="Wordpress"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-329" title="wordpress" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/wordpress.jpg" alt="" width="238" height="212" /></a></p>
<p>WordPress, one of the most popular blogging tool and publishing platform provides endless ways for bloggers to edit some minor details of their posts. It&#8217;s just a matter of exploring wp-admin page.</p>
<p>I must admit that I, myself, once had trouble looking for a button, a link or something that will let me change the author of a particular post. It took me minutes navigating the admin page with no luck until a dropdown that says &#8216;Bulk Actions&#8217; on the upper left corner of the post listing caught my attention. It is then that I learned that its function is to quickly manipulate your posts&#8217; settings. The following can be edited using WordPress&#8217;  Bulk Actions (Edit):</p>
<ul>
<li>Categories (select from existing categories)</li>
<li>Post Tags (add more tags for your post)</li>
<li>Author (select from a dropdown of  admin page users)</li>
<li>Comments (allow or do not allow commenting for particular post(s))</li>
<li>Status (published, private/public, pending review, draft)</li>
<li>Pings (allow or do not allow pings)</li>
<li>Sticky (sticky or not sticky)</li>
</ul>
<p>The Edit pane will open after selecting posts to edit, selecting Edit from Bulk Actions dropdown and clicking the Apply button.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
