		<title>PHP Snippets: Resolving IE Facebook session issue</title>
		<link>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/php-snippets-resolving-ie-facebook-session-issue</link>
		<comments>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/php-snippets-resolving-ie-facebook-session-issue#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Sat, 07 May 2011 15:50:35 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Web]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[facebook]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[facebook application]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Internet Explorer]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[PHP]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=267</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/php-snippets-resolving-ie-facebook-session-issue"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/php.png" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="" title="php" /></a>Facebook continuously updates its proprietary SDK (Facebook SDK). Part of it are some issues that are sometimes hard for developers to understand why it&#8217;s happening. Here&#8217;s an example. For some reason, Facebook session is lost when browsing your fb application using Internet Explorer. This causes the redirection to the login url  which then redirects back to the application page. All other browsers work perfectly but IE. Here&#8217;s a solution. The workaround is so simple. You just need to add this[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/php.png" rel="lightbox" title="PHP"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-212" title="php" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/php.png" alt="" width="184" height="113" /></a></p>
<p>Facebook continuously updates its proprietary SDK (Facebook SDK). Part of it are some issues that are sometimes hard for developers to understand why it&#8217;s happening. Here&#8217;s an example. For some reason, Facebook session is lost when browsing your fb application using Internet Explorer. This causes the redirection to the login url  which then redirects back to the application page. All other browsers work perfectly but IE.</p>
<p>Here&#8217;s a solution. The workaround is so simple. You just need to add this header on top of your PHP script and you&#8217;re good to go.</p>
<pre>header('P3P:CP="IDC DSP COR ADM DEVi TAIi PSA PSD IVAi IVDi CONi HIS OUR IND CNT"');</pre>
<p>More snippets soon so watch out!</p>
