		<title>Symbian Anna</title>
		<link>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/symbian-anna</link>
		<comments>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/symbian-anna#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 28 Apr 2011 16:51:49 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Mobile]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Softwares]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Technology]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Nokia]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Nokia C6-01]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Nokia C7]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Nokia E6]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Nokia E7]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Nokia N8]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Nokia X7]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Symbian Anna]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Symbian OS]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=218</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/symbian-anna"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Symbian-Anna-300x168.jpg" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="" title="Symbian Anna" /></a>Photo Credits: Nokia Conversation Nokia recently launched its latest lineup of smartphones &#8211; the Nokia X7 and Nokia E6, and the arrival of the new version of the Symbian operating system synchronously. Initially named as PR2, the renewed version of the mobile operating system is now called Symbian Anna which comes with a faster browser,  updated version of Ovi Maps, enhanced text inputs, and had the icons have brand new looks. New Icons: the new version of Symbian OS comes[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Symbian-Anna.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-219" title="Symbian Anna" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Symbian-Anna-300x168.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="168" /></a><br />
<small>Photo Credits: Nokia Conversation</small></p>
<p>Nokia recently launched its latest lineup of smartphones &#8211; the Nokia X7 and Nokia E6, and the arrival of the new version of the Symbian operating system synchronously. Initially named as PR2, the renewed version of the mobile operating system is now called Symbian Anna which comes with a faster browser,  updated version of Ovi Maps, enhanced text inputs, and had the icons have brand new looks.</p>
<p><strong>New Icons:</strong><br />
the new version of Symbian OS comes with new icons which is its most prominent update from the previous versions.</p>
<p><strong>Better Ovi Maps (v3.06):</strong><br />
smarter search; Check-in to Facebook,  Twitter, Foursquareor local social networks; ability to share places via  email and SMS, and also with friends using non-Nokia phones; public  transport network lines view; update and download full country maps via  WLAN</p>
<p><strong>Enhanced Browser (v7.3):</strong><br />
high value touch UI improvements, including URL  entry bar, always visible ‘Go Back’ and extended toolbar buttons and  search-integrated address field; better user responsiveness, faster  history navigation and page loading, split screen virtual Qwerty  keyboard.</p>
<p><strong>Improved Text Inputs:</strong><br />
there’s the long-awaited portrait QWERTY input, plus a split screen when  entering text into web pages and apps, so you don’t lose sight of what  you’re filling in.</p>
<p>For developers, the following mobile technologies are available for Symbian Anna:</p>
<ul>
<li>Flashlite 4</li>
<li>Java Runtime 2.2</li>
<li>Qt Mobility 1.1</li>
<li>Qt 4.7</li>
</ul>
<p>Symbian Anna is made available only to the two new smartphones but will eventually be installable to Nokia N8, C7, C6-01 and E7 though Nokia did not announce when will this be yet.</p>
<fb:like href=http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/symbian-anna font=></fb:like>]]></content:encoded>
