		<title>Adding thumbnail, title and description in sharing links on Facebook</title>
		<link>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/adding-thumbnail-title-and-description-in-sharing-links-on-facebook</link>
		<comments>http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/adding-thumbnail-title-and-description-in-sharing-links-on-facebook#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Tue, 26 Apr 2011 15:56:40 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Web]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[facebook]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[share meta tags]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=189</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/adding-thumbnail-title-and-description-in-sharing-links-on-facebook"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Facebook-Share-300x209.jpg" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="" title="Facebook Share" /></a>Sharing links to social networking sites has been an instrument of viral campaigns, promotions and even on a simple wall post. Facebook stands out in terms of how links are shared over the popular social networking site because of its ability to pull data (thumbnail image, title and description) asynchronously from the URL that is being shared by the user among its counterparts. Sometimes, these information, most frequently the image, are missing when sharing links due to some restrictions. Don&#8217;t[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Facebook-Share.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-190" title="Facebook Share" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Facebook-Share-300x209.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="209" /></a></p>
<p>Sharing links to social networking sites has been an instrument of viral campaigns, promotions and even on a simple wall post. Facebook stands out in terms of how links are shared over the popular social networking site because of its ability to pull data (thumbnail image, title and description) asynchronously from the URL that is being shared by the user among its counterparts. Sometimes, these information, most frequently the image, are missing when sharing links due to some restrictions. Don&#8217;t worry, this post will provide you with tips to get the links you share more catchy with thumbnail, title and description on them.</p>
<p>The idea is simple. You just need to add these information to your  tags in your markup to tell Facebook to show these information when shared.</p>
<pre> &lt;meta name="title" content="your title here" /&gt;
 &lt;meta name="description" content="yourdescription here " /&gt;
 &lt;link rel="image_src" href="thumbnail_image source" / &gt;</pre>
<fb:like href=http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/adding-thumbnail-title-and-description-in-sharing-links-on-facebook font=></fb:like>]]></content:encoded>
