				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/hero20110302.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-165" title="hero20110302" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/hero20110302-300x85.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="85" /></a><br />
<small>Photo Credits: Apple.com</small></p>
<p>Apple just released the latest update for iOS. &#8220;The most advanced mobile operating system&#8221;, as what Apple claims iOS to be, is now on its 4.3.2 version and is available for free download. The latest free update contains software improvement and fixes some bugs. Some of which are the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>Fixes an issue that occasionally caused blank or frozen video during a FaceTime call</li>
<li>Fixes an issue that prevented some international users from connecting to 3G networks on iPad Wi-Fi + 3G</li>
<li>Contains the latest security updates</li>
</ul>
<p>Below are the devices made compatible for the update:</p>
<ul>
<li>iPhone 4 (GSM model)</li>
<li>iPhone 3GS</li>
<li>iPad 2</li>
<li>iPad</li>
<li>iPod touch (4th generation)</li>
<li>iPod touch (3rd generation)</li>
</ul>
<p>The software update takes up to 650MB free space.</p>
