		<category><![CDATA[facebook fan page]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[iframe application]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/?p=89</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<a href="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/add-facebook-application-to-your-fan-page"><img align="left" hspace="5" width="150" height="150" src="http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/wp-content/plugins/thumbnail-for-excerpts/tfe_no_thumb.png" class="alignleft wp-post-image tfe" alt="" title="" /></a>Adding a Facebook application to your fan page tab is simple. Just follow these simple steps: Browse for the application you wish to add to your fan page tab from the application directory (http://www.facebook.com/apps/directory.php). If you manage or are a developer of the desired application, you may go directly to the developers page (http://www.facebook.com/developers). Go to the application&#8217;s profile page and look for &#8216;Add to My Page&#8217; link on the left rail part of the profile page. A popup dialog[...]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Adding a Facebook application to your fan page tab is simple. Just follow these simple steps:</p>
<ol>
<li>Browse for the application you wish to add to your fan page tab from the application directory (http://www.facebook.com/apps/directory.php). If you manage or are a developer of the desired application, you may go directly to the developers page (http://www.facebook.com/developers).</li>
<li>Go to the application&#8217;s profile page and look for &#8216;Add to My Page&#8217; link on the left rail part of the profile page. A popup dialog box then appears showing all the pages you manage.</li>
<li>Click on the &#8216;Add to Page&#8217; next to the page you want the application to be contained in.</li>
<li>View the page(s) where the application was added to check if it really were. Enjoy!</li>
</ol>
<fb:like href=http://blogs.coldbuffer.com/add-facebook-application-to-your-fan-page font=></fb:like>]]></content:encoded>
